com.hyperwallet.android

Interface HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenListener


  • public interface HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenListener
    A callback interface to handle the submission of an authentication token or an error message in the case of a failure.

    Authentication tokens will be used until they expire.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onFailure(UUID uuid, String message)
      Notifies the Hyperwallet SDK of a failure to generate an authentication token.
      void onSuccess(String authenticationToken)
      Sets the authentication token to be used when contacting the Hyperwallet platform.

    • Method Detail

      • onSuccess

        void onSuccess(String authenticationToken)
        Sets the authentication token to be used when contacting the Hyperwallet platform. The authentication token is a JSON web token that contains as part of its claim set the principal that will be interacting with the Hyperwallet platform.
        Parameters:
        authenticationToken - a JWT token identifying a Hyperwallet User principal

      • onFailure

        void onFailure(UUID uuid,
               String message)
        Notifies the Hyperwallet SDK of a failure to generate an authentication token. The message along with the universally unique id are used to track the occurrence of authentication token retrieval failures.
        Parameters:
        uuid - a universally unique identifier
        message - indicating the cause of the authentication token retrieval error
